  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AB Bank Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will have a high development impact considering that microfinance has been shown to play a major role in poverty and unemployment reduction in developing countries. The project will provide MSMEs in Rwanda with greater access to finance, create economic opportunities and develop the local economy. In addition, the project will promote commercial oriented microfinance in Rwanda and provide a strong demonstration to the microfinance sector.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project consists of an equity investment and a local currency loan to support the creation and expansion of a microfinance bank in Rwanda, AB Bank Rwanda Limited (ABR). ABR will be a greenfield microfinance bank sponsored by Access Microfinance Holding AG (AccessHolding), an investment company, and LFS Financial Systems, an associated German consulting firm with recognized expertise in microfinance. The Bank will specialize in providing a broad range of financial services to urban and semi-urban micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs) as well as low income individuals in Rwanda. It is expected that after five years the Bank will have ten branches, a loan portfolio of US$32 million, comprising over 25,000 customers.</narrative>
  </description>
